#############################################
# 15/04/08 - Added ability to inject NPC characters 
via Spring configs
#############################################

Added ability to inject new non-player characters via the Spring bean configuration for a game.

#############################################
# 15/04/08 - Moved Input and player instantiation
#############################################

Input object is now held by the Avatar to enable switching and resuming use of Avatars (switching squad members/cars etc).
Player object instantiated from Spring bean not explicitly in code.

#############################################
# 15/04/08 - final changes before needing to
refactor the behaviour interfaces.
#############################################

These are the last sets of changes before i have to refactor the behaviours to integrate
fully with the AI library's steering methods, checking in now so i can roll back easily if necessary.

#############################################
# 14/04/08 - Server webapp service 'wired' 
via Spring beans.
#############################################

Added support methods to server-side classes to allow game to be 'wired' using Spring bean definition file.
aereon.xml config file contains simple definitions for a single zone.

#############################################
# 14/04/08 - Added the initial classes for 
the server-side AI library.
#############################################

#############################################
# 14/04/08 - Initial changes made to the server 
webapp in preperation for integrating with Jedai.
#############################################

Client input is now handled by a Red5 'service' rather than the Application class.
Fixed bug in input handling on server side, Player object now updates its avatar until it's time matches that of the client. Client input need not be sent continually now, only when it's changed.
Changed 'Room' object to more generic name 'Zone'.
Zones use the strategy pattern to handle player input, each Avatar in the Zone is manipulated by a behaviour that implements the IAvatarBehaviour interface. This brings the server in line with the client side, in preperation for Actionscript support in Red5.

#############################################
# 09/04/08 - Modified the synchronisation method.
#############################################

Proxy object now holds the correct Input data so if there's a gap in server 
response the proxy will continue to move with the last input set instead of
becoming stationary.

#############################################
# 08/04/08 - Added destroy() methods.
#############################################

Added destroy methods to the Avatar and it's descendants to make sure that 
objects are cleared for GC as well as possible when a remote player disconnects.

#############################################
# 07/04/08 - Refactored server code.
#############################################

The server was returning the wrong classname for the player's object - causing the player
to throw an error. Fixed this.

#############################################
# 06/04/08 - Added space station and planet
objects to default Aereon scene.
#############################################

Added space station and planet models into the default Aereon scene so we can publish a
basic demo of the framework in action and have some frame of reference for players - with no
models there's no sense of speed at all.

#############################################
# 06/04/08 - Fixed SWFObject FireFox bug
#############################################

Fixed SWFObject firefox bug using fix from SwfObject google code pages.

Added ability for new project build script to dynamically create a stub actionscript file
for the new game created.

#############################################
# 04/04/08 - Updated new project build script
#############################################

Updated the new project build mechanism to ensure it builds a new project that keeps to the new locale setup. 

Tidied up the global build properties file.

